## Description {#details}

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectortemplatebase">SmallVectorTemplateBase</a>&lt;TriviallyCopyable = false&gt; - This is where we put method implementations that are designed to work with non-trivial T&#39;s.

We approximate is&#95;trivially&#95;copyable with trivial move/copy construction and trivial destruction. While the standard doesn&#39;t specify that you&#39;re allowed copy these types with memcpy, there is no way for the type to observe this. This catches the important case of std::pair&lt;POD, POD&gt;, which is not trivially assignable.

Definition at line 329 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/smallvector-h">SmallVector.h</a>.
